ing: 2 (15.5 ounce) cans garbanzo beans, drained, liquid reserved
3 fresh jalapeno chiles, with seeds and ribs removed
des: "This super yummy, fiesta-style hummus tastes just like guacamole, but it's much more flavorful. It's also easy to make. Just combine the ingredients in a food processor; measurements don't need to be exact."
ins: Place the garbanzo beans, garlic, tahini, salt, orange juice, jalapeno chiles, avocado, and cilantro in the bowl of a food processor. Process until smooth. Adjust thickness by stirring in desired amount of reserved liquid from garbanzo beans or olive oil. Refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.
